<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-5315] Stack overflow in PDColorSpace.create()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5315</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4833&quot; title=&quot;PDColorSpace#create IOException, expected a name or array but got COSDictionary&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4833&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4833&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (handling of dictionary with /ColorSpace entry) introduces an infinite recursion bug in case the referenced dictionary is the color space itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Extract of a pdf that triggers the bug (see attachment):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;18 0 obj&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;&amp;lt;/Type/XObject/Subtype/Image/Width 2794/Height 928/SMask 3 0 R/Length 13428/BitsPerComponent 8/Filter/FlateDecode/ColorSpace &lt;b&gt;18 0 R&lt;/b&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
